That's why there's a Goy whose God is

01:16:20.715 --> 01:16:23.216
Jehovah.

01:16:23.235 --> 01:16:25.195
Because that wrong had to be righted.

01:16:26.417 --> 01:16:30.417
Dowd had to be reintroduced as our savior,

01:16:30.518 --> 01:16:31.838
as the Passover lamb.

01:16:33.105 --> 01:16:34.846
as the one who carried our guilt into

01:16:34.886 --> 01:16:37.387
shield to perfect us,

01:16:38.128 --> 01:16:42.871
as the firstborn of firstborn children,

01:16:42.951 --> 01:16:46.412
as the one that we can follow to

01:16:46.432 --> 01:16:49.413
Yahowah and be enriched and empowered,

01:16:49.453 --> 01:16:50.175
becoming great.

01:16:52.195 --> 01:16:54.096
Someone would have to reflect his

01:16:54.157 --> 01:16:54.777
brilliance.

01:16:58.618 --> 01:17:01.020
And that's what delivered Dowd from the

01:17:01.119 --> 01:17:02.581
anxiety and the concern

01:17:04.976 --> 01:17:06.759
You see this too in Yasha'yah.

01:17:07.761 --> 01:17:12.386
When he finally sees that man from Edom,

01:17:12.927 --> 01:17:13.609
Obed-Edom,

01:17:13.788 --> 01:17:16.032
who was tasked with the responsibility of

01:17:16.072 --> 01:17:17.453
bringing the Ark of the Covenant,

01:17:17.493 --> 01:17:20.016
positioning it so that Dowd can anoint it.

01:17:21.131 --> 01:17:23.634
And he finally sees that all of the

01:17:23.694 --> 01:17:25.975
prophecies and promises and insights that

01:17:26.015 --> 01:17:26.876
he has delivered,

01:17:27.355 --> 01:17:29.396
which have not resonated with a single

01:17:29.457 --> 01:17:29.898
Yahuwd,

01:17:29.997 --> 01:17:32.118
not a single person in all of this

01:17:32.139 --> 01:17:34.020
time and have been corrupted by the

01:17:34.060 --> 01:17:35.921
religious, particularly by Christians,

01:17:37.622 --> 01:17:40.104
that he finally sees this man from Edom,

01:17:41.104 --> 01:17:42.064
the final Zarowa,

01:17:43.006 --> 01:17:46.809
the Choter that he devoted a chapter to,

01:17:47.948 --> 01:17:50.490
the Nakry, this observant foreigner,

01:17:52.076 --> 01:17:54.737
a very cold voice calling out in the

01:17:54.777 --> 01:17:58.096
wilderness, that he arrives.

01:17:58.997 --> 01:18:01.997
And Isaiah is so ecstatic, he says,

01:18:02.137 --> 01:18:03.438
that's my Zarowa.

01:18:03.939 --> 01:18:05.219
That's my guy.

01:18:06.399 --> 01:18:08.159
He is now in that wine vat with

01:18:08.220 --> 01:18:08.399
me.

01:18:09.359 --> 01:18:10.399
He's going to save many.

01:18:11.180 --> 01:18:11.479
In fact,

01:18:11.520 --> 01:18:13.560
I even think it's we're going to save

01:18:13.621 --> 01:18:16.440
many because he's reciting Yasha'yah

01:18:16.461 --> 01:18:18.421
script.

01:18:18.442 --> 01:18:19.502
Yasha'yah delineated it.

01:18:22.565 --> 01:18:25.988
this is all one integrated story and it

01:18:26.087 --> 01:18:30.470
is the story that I'm telling and coming

01:18:30.489 --> 01:18:35.011
home for the opening paragraph of that

01:18:35.112 --> 01:18:40.954
volume says that there are two truths that

01:18:40.975 --> 01:18:46.317
are essential for you to know that

01:18:46.337 --> 01:18:50.158
Yahowah's beloved son the anointed messiah

01:18:51.578 --> 01:18:53.399
our former and returning king,

01:18:55.079 --> 01:18:57.442
who fulfilled Pesach, Matsah, and Bikuwrym,

01:18:58.301 --> 01:19:00.963
providing us with eternal light, life,

01:19:01.043 --> 01:19:01.583
perfection,

01:19:02.505 --> 01:19:05.587
and adoption into God's family,

01:19:05.627 --> 01:19:06.648
is none other than Dowd,

01:19:06.667 --> 01:19:12.430
who the world knows as David.

01:19:12.451 --> 01:19:17.373
And that since the world has ripped him

01:19:17.475 --> 01:19:19.655
off, robbed him, plundered him,

01:19:20.136 --> 01:19:21.096
denied him,

01:19:23.706 --> 01:19:24.947
All of these accolades.

01:19:26.528 --> 01:19:27.328
And achievements.

01:19:28.529 --> 01:19:29.010
Stealing.

01:19:29.850 --> 01:19:32.953
His very titles.

01:19:32.993 --> 01:19:33.394
From him.

01:19:34.595 --> 01:19:35.635
Through identity theft.

01:19:37.777 --> 01:19:38.478
That God.

01:19:40.019 --> 01:19:40.819
Spoke of another.

01:19:42.621 --> 01:19:43.381
Who would bring.

01:19:44.822 --> 01:19:45.743
The dignity.

01:19:46.444 --> 01:19:47.404
Back to doubt.

01:19:48.265 --> 01:19:49.126
And by doing so.

01:19:50.469 --> 01:19:53.411
point to all that Dowd has accomplished

01:19:53.650 --> 01:19:57.033
through his father to provide

01:19:57.432 --> 01:20:01.775
reconciliation in the fractured family and

01:20:01.815 --> 01:20:04.978
bring God's people back together to

01:20:05.037 --> 01:20:08.020
recognize that his God is Yahowah and that

01:20:08.079 --> 01:20:11.462
together they achieved everything that

01:20:11.521 --> 01:20:13.983
needed to be done for us to live

01:20:14.523 --> 01:20:17.005
forever in their company.

01:20:19.818 --> 01:20:20.478
It took two.

01:20:24.060 --> 01:20:28.722
And these two souls stand out from all

01:20:28.802 --> 01:20:35.306
others.

01:20:35.407 --> 01:20:40.189
One of the many things which made Dowd

01:20:42.591 --> 01:20:45.971
exceptionally unique, of course,

01:20:46.051 --> 01:20:48.134
during his first life that he would grow

01:20:48.154 --> 01:20:48.673
with Yahowah,

01:20:50.202 --> 01:20:53.064
was his thirst for Torah teaching.

01:20:55.265 --> 01:20:58.328
In the third volume of An Introduction to

01:20:58.389 --> 01:21:03.592
God, volume three, it's called Torah,

01:21:04.774 --> 01:21:10.497
and the preponderance of it is written to

01:21:10.597 --> 01:21:16.243
disclose and to examine, to learn from,

01:21:17.184 --> 01:21:19.405
Dowd's hundred and nineteenth Mizmowr
.

01:21:20.167 --> 01:21:21.529
which is his ode to the Torah.

01:21:23.829 --> 01:21:28.231
He wrote eight lines regarding each of the

01:21:28.271 --> 01:21:30.412
twenty-two letters in the Hebrew alphabet

01:21:30.533 --> 01:21:33.734
in alphabetical order to describe how we

01:21:33.795 --> 01:21:37.317
should observe Yahowah's Torah teaching.

01:21:38.237 --> 01:21:38.577
Brilliant.

01:21:39.898 --> 01:21:44.880
He wrote the nineteenth Mizmowr
 as sort of

01:21:44.899 --> 01:21:47.081
the cliff notes to say, you know,

01:21:47.100 --> 01:21:48.221
the Torah is perfect.

01:21:50.188 --> 01:21:51.229
Restores the soul.

01:21:53.153 --> 01:21:55.235
And between these two,

01:21:56.518 --> 01:22:02.527
it was darn near perfection in terms of

01:22:02.567 --> 01:22:03.988
explaining God's guidance.

01:22:05.110 --> 01:22:05.610
Dowd, of course,

01:22:05.631 --> 01:22:09.253
would also write the Mizmowr that convinced

01:22:09.314 --> 01:22:11.095
me to say yes to Yahowah.

01:22:11.814 --> 01:22:12.855
When I said,

01:22:13.235 --> 01:22:14.417
you want me to do what?

01:22:15.117 --> 01:22:17.137
No one has ever survived that before.

01:22:17.759 --> 01:22:18.198
Thank you.

01:22:19.319 --> 01:22:23.542
God, I can't say no.

01:22:23.561 --> 01:22:24.882
But we need to negotiate.

01:22:25.162 --> 01:22:26.163
Can we negotiate?

01:22:26.684 --> 01:22:28.005
Will you allow me to negotiate?

01:22:28.024 --> 01:22:28.685
Sure, what do you want?

01:22:29.365 --> 01:22:30.405
Well, I want these three things.

01:22:30.466 --> 01:22:31.627
Okay, reach into your pocket.

01:22:32.448 --> 01:22:34.488
Dowd wrote the psalm that was in my

01:22:34.548 --> 01:22:34.849
pocket.

01:22:36.184 --> 01:22:39.186
And it's the one that said, yeah,

01:22:39.207 --> 01:22:41.389
you're willing to do these things with me.

01:22:41.829 --> 01:22:45.193
I will do these things for you.

01:22:45.313 --> 01:22:47.154
I knew what you were going to ask

01:22:47.996 --> 01:22:50.318
three thousand years before you asked.

01:22:53.240 --> 01:22:54.622
Because we've had a relationship for a

01:22:54.641 --> 01:22:55.342
very long time.

01:23:03.166 --> 01:23:04.787
The more Dowd, of course,

01:23:04.847 --> 01:23:05.988
read in the Torah,

01:23:06.029 --> 01:23:08.712
the more reflective of God's nature he

01:23:08.752 --> 01:23:09.072
became.

01:23:10.753 --> 01:23:11.514
It is in this way,

01:23:11.573 --> 01:23:12.635
by studying the Torah,

01:23:12.675 --> 01:23:14.657
that the Messiah found the answers,

01:23:14.717 --> 01:23:17.961
including why he should be the one who

01:23:18.001 --> 01:23:20.483
volunteers to serve as the Pesach Geo.

01:23:22.805 --> 01:23:23.546
And truly,

01:23:23.565 --> 01:23:25.387
it's how Yahowah responds to us today.

01:23:26.009 --> 01:23:27.010
It's how we listen to him.

01:23:28.612 --> 01:23:31.814
Dowd's life to an extent well beyond most

01:23:32.033 --> 01:23:34.655
of our own was filled with monumental

01:23:34.695 --> 01:23:36.557
challenges.

01:23:36.837 --> 01:23:37.497
Some of these,

01:23:37.557 --> 01:23:39.859
particularly in the stress of battle or

01:23:39.960 --> 01:23:41.881
while sharing insights into his

01:23:41.942 --> 01:23:43.141
relationship with God,

01:23:43.943 --> 01:23:46.625
when all were opposed to him,

01:23:46.704 --> 01:23:49.627
he navigated most of them gloriously.

01:23:52.529 --> 01:23:54.730
But he was not consistently great

01:23:56.307 --> 01:23:58.569
when dealing with political and family

01:23:58.609 --> 01:24:01.631
issues.

01:24:01.850 --> 01:24:02.351
At times,

01:24:02.412 --> 01:24:07.333
he allowed his anxiety over challenges

01:24:07.373 --> 01:24:10.877
that he or Yahowah could have resolved

01:24:11.197 --> 01:24:16.060
really expeditiously drag on to the point

01:24:16.100 --> 01:24:17.359
they became distracting and

01:24:17.420 --> 01:24:18.161
counterproductive.

01:24:20.046 --> 01:24:21.686
Clearly, all's well that ends well,

01:24:21.827 --> 01:24:24.128
and Dowd's story ends gloriously.

01:24:24.588 --> 01:24:26.610
Dowd's journey was considerably less

01:24:26.671 --> 01:24:29.712
tranquil than he is, of course,

01:24:29.752 --> 01:24:31.475
leading on in this moment.

01:24:32.636 --> 01:24:35.738
And that's essential because everyone who

01:24:35.858 --> 01:24:38.399
works with Yahowah grows with him.

01:24:39.961 --> 01:24:43.143
We fail at times, we're wrong at times,

01:24:44.323 --> 01:24:45.524
and through it all, we grow.

01:24:46.605 --> 01:24:47.546
We develop a backbone.

01:24:49.365 --> 01:24:53.948
Our character is forged in the fires of

01:24:54.009 --> 01:24:54.390
challenges.

01:24:54.449 --> 01:24:58.431
And we don't always get it right.

01:24:59.573 --> 01:25:00.953
And we have to learn lessons.

01:25:02.335 --> 01:25:07.198
We actually have to experience the most

01:25:07.618 --> 01:25:11.319
embittering of all human emotions,

01:25:11.340 --> 01:25:13.662
which is the abuse of a fractured family.

01:25:15.793 --> 01:25:17.335
because otherwise we're not in a position

01:25:17.354 --> 01:25:18.154
to speak for God.

01:25:18.595 --> 01:25:20.195
We don't understand what he has gone

01:25:20.235 --> 01:25:21.997
through these six thousand years.

01:25:23.057 --> 01:25:28.820
So all of this is vitally important for

01:25:28.900 --> 01:25:29.161
us.

01:25:31.242 --> 01:25:34.823
Something for us to know about even Dowd,

01:25:34.844 --> 01:25:39.086
the closest person in human existence to

01:25:39.166 --> 01:25:41.846
his father, is that even Dowd grew.

01:25:45.520 --> 01:25:50.221
developed character made mistakes got up

01:25:51.061 --> 01:25:55.722
learned from them and moved on it's what

01:25:55.762 --> 01:25:58.884
makes him real it's what means that what

01:25:58.923 --> 01:26:00.884
this means is that when we're paired

01:26:00.923 --> 01:26:03.765
together through eternity we are in a

01:26:03.864 --> 01:26:08.587
position where we can be comfortable

01:26:08.627 --> 01:26:10.726
together you know he is not up here

01:26:10.806 --> 01:26:13.688
and we're down here we're working together

01:26:16.686 --> 01:26:19.207
Comfortable together, helping one another,

01:26:20.668 --> 01:26:21.989
more together than we would be

01:26:22.050 --> 01:26:22.670
individually.

01:26:25.292 --> 01:26:25.971
Now, personally,

01:26:26.072 --> 01:26:29.073
apart from attacks on my credibility when

01:26:29.134 --> 01:26:30.774
speaking for Yahowah, which are many,

01:26:31.994 --> 01:26:34.817
or the merit of Yada Yahowah,

01:26:35.457 --> 01:26:37.978
it's rare that I fret over much of

01:26:38.037 --> 01:26:38.859
anything else,

01:26:39.139 --> 01:26:42.680
unless you're trying to disparage me

01:26:44.921 --> 01:26:47.622
recognizing that credibility is the

01:26:47.662 --> 01:26:49.944
currency of this program,

01:26:50.585 --> 01:26:52.827
of writing on behalf of, yeah, well,

01:26:53.427 --> 01:26:54.488
I really don't fret it.

01:26:54.627 --> 01:26:55.448
I don't care.

01:26:55.609 --> 01:26:59.192
You know, I learned many,

01:26:59.212 --> 01:27:00.993
many years ago that if you Google my

01:27:01.052 --> 01:27:01.373
name,

01:27:01.594 --> 01:27:03.335
you'll find that there's millions of

01:27:03.574 --> 01:27:06.197
people who obviously have no clue who I

01:27:06.256 --> 01:27:10.079
am, but seem to have opinions.

01:27:10.199 --> 01:27:12.561
It's what happens if you live your life

01:27:12.601 --> 01:27:13.603
with your head above the crowd.

01:27:16.890 --> 01:27:17.690
And in all of that time,

01:27:17.730 --> 01:27:19.431
I've learned that I really don't care.

01:27:19.712 --> 01:27:22.033
And the only time I care is when

01:27:22.212 --> 01:27:26.335
somebody besmirches my reputation in

01:27:26.375 --> 01:27:28.676
association with my work on behalf of

01:27:28.756 --> 01:27:30.317
Yahowah and Yadda Yahowah.

01:27:30.938 --> 01:27:32.478
Because again,

01:27:33.559 --> 01:27:35.520
credibility when associated with God is

01:27:35.579 --> 01:27:39.601
the currency of our success.

01:27:39.622 --> 01:27:41.443
But the other stuff I don't care about.

01:27:41.962 --> 01:27:43.564
Disappointments, yes, I've...

01:27:44.537 --> 01:27:47.757
had my share and more than enough

01:27:47.797 --> 01:27:51.378
challenges to surmount for a lifetime.

01:27:53.680 --> 01:27:56.740
And yet I'm always confident expecting a

01:27:56.820 --> 01:27:57.881
favorable resolution.

01:27:57.921 --> 01:27:59.801
We've gone through difficult times and we

01:27:59.820 --> 01:28:00.981
have always prevailed.

01:28:01.481 --> 01:28:03.403
So particularly now when collaborating

01:28:03.443 --> 01:28:06.222
with the Iowa to this extent at this

01:28:06.262 --> 01:28:08.163
time, my confidence source,

01:28:09.520 --> 01:28:11.961
Therefore, I concur with Do's conclusion.

01:28:12.561 --> 01:28:14.483
Yahowah always delivers.

01:28:15.363 --> 01:28:16.604
And with Yah,

01:28:17.123 --> 01:28:18.765
we really have nothing to be concerned

01:28:18.805 --> 01:28:19.064
about.

01:28:20.765 --> 01:28:22.587
Yeah, with one exception,

01:28:22.627 --> 01:28:23.726
and that is that we are human.

01:28:25.467 --> 01:28:26.588
The pressures are immense.

01:28:27.929 --> 01:28:29.189
The audience is hostile.

01:28:30.711 --> 01:28:33.452
And it takes a lot out of a

01:28:33.511 --> 01:28:35.472
person when you're constantly whack,

01:28:35.573 --> 01:28:36.554
whack, whack.

01:28:37.694 --> 01:28:38.875
It took...

01:28:39.850 --> 01:28:42.051
Moshe, who's a far greater man than I,

01:28:43.092 --> 01:28:46.155
and it wore him down to the point

01:28:46.216 --> 01:28:47.197
he asked God to kill him.

01:28:48.618 --> 01:28:51.140
It took Do to the point that he

01:28:51.180 --> 01:28:54.585
turned into mush by the end of the

01:28:54.704 --> 01:29:00.029
Absalom rebellion.

01:29:00.890 --> 01:29:01.431
It's tough.

01:29:03.587 --> 01:29:04.447
And so, you know,

01:29:04.587 --> 01:29:06.847
I try to pace myself.

01:29:06.868 --> 01:29:08.948
I talk to Rich about this all the

01:29:08.988 --> 01:29:12.469
time, that we have to pace ourselves.

01:29:12.748 --> 01:29:13.189
You know,

01:29:13.889 --> 01:29:15.829
it is an all-in game in the sense

01:29:15.869 --> 01:29:19.190
that sunrise to sunset, seven days a week,

01:29:19.211 --> 01:29:20.890
we're at this one way or another.

01:29:21.451 --> 01:29:25.332
But it can't all be before this camera.

01:29:26.451 --> 01:29:29.293
It can't all be in social media where

01:29:29.314 --> 01:29:32.355
we're so subject to criticism and attack

01:29:32.536 --> 01:29:33.636
all the time.

01:29:35.158 --> 01:29:36.619
Part of it has to be growing with

01:29:36.659 --> 01:29:38.862
God, studying his testimony,

01:29:39.762 --> 01:29:44.106
analyzing his words, writing, learning,

01:29:44.726 --> 01:29:45.408
and then sharing.

01:29:50.391 --> 01:29:50.532
So...

01:29:52.872 --> 01:29:54.273
I know that Yahowah will deliver the

01:29:54.912 --> 01:29:56.453
intended result because we've already read

01:29:56.493 --> 01:29:56.833
about it.

01:29:57.694 --> 01:29:58.993
So it all boils down to this.

01:29:59.613 --> 01:30:04.135
We must learn to know and then know

01:30:04.194 --> 01:30:04.635
to grow.

01:30:05.854 --> 01:30:08.095
We travel to Yahowah in our minds,

01:30:08.716 --> 01:30:11.436
relying on his words to guide us.

01:30:12.657 --> 01:30:15.777
And once there, happiness happens.

01:30:17.898 --> 01:30:18.957
Productivity is assured.

01:30:21.653 --> 01:30:25.614
I don't wanna sugar coat this though.

01:30:25.654 --> 01:30:26.735
Happiness does happen.

01:30:27.655 --> 01:30:29.077
Productivity is assured.

01:30:29.896 --> 01:30:31.797
That does not mean that every day is

01:30:32.037 --> 01:30:35.078
sunshine and tulips.

01:30:35.158 --> 01:30:35.698
It just isn't.

01:30:37.119 --> 01:30:37.779
Life is tough.

01:30:39.140 --> 01:30:41.141
And if you're going to be with God

01:30:41.202 --> 01:30:42.743
and gonna spend eternity with him,

01:30:43.162 --> 01:30:44.643
he wants you tested and true.

01:30:45.923 --> 01:30:47.085
He wants you to have some grit.

01:30:48.104 --> 01:30:49.786
And so there will be challenges to

01:30:49.865 --> 01:30:50.265
overcome.

01:30:51.488 --> 01:30:54.310
And this happily ever after happens,

01:30:54.850 --> 01:30:58.314
but it doesn't happen until we enter the

01:30:58.873 --> 01:31:01.796
restoration of the conditions experienced

01:31:01.876 --> 01:31:07.980
in Eden, on Sukah, on October seventh,

01:31:08.282 --> 01:31:10.684
a Shabbat, in year six thousand, yeah,

01:31:10.724 --> 01:31:13.166
twenty thirty three.

01:31:13.405 --> 01:31:14.065
And at that point.

01:31:16.148 --> 01:31:19.791
We will know nothing but joy.

01:31:19.831 --> 01:31:20.490
Because all of the.

01:31:21.390 --> 01:31:23.171
anguishing individuals will be gone.

01:31:26.432 --> 01:31:29.274
And I think at an hour and thirty

01:31:29.413 --> 01:31:29.854
one minutes,

01:31:29.895 --> 01:31:31.694
this is probably the right place for us

01:31:31.755 --> 01:31:33.935
to conclude this program.

01:31:33.975 --> 01:31:36.698
We have just made our way through the

01:31:37.118 --> 01:31:39.538
fourth statement of

01:31:39.578 --> 01:31:43.621
Mizmowr song, thirty four through thirty four,

01:31:43.961 --> 01:31:45.520
one, two, three and four.

01:31:45.560 --> 01:31:46.942
We're about to start five,

01:31:47.301 --> 01:31:48.802
but I think I'm going to postpone five.

01:31:50.301 --> 01:31:54.002
There's a lot to learn in this song.

01:31:54.563 --> 01:31:56.323
And I would much prefer that we go

01:31:56.363 --> 01:31:58.585
through it methodically and that we glean

01:31:58.625 --> 01:32:00.824
everything that we can from it and that

01:32:00.864 --> 01:32:02.506
we grow as a result of it.

01:32:02.905 --> 01:32:05.646
Because here we have just been told that

01:32:05.766 --> 01:32:10.828
it is Dowd's soul that is glowing with

01:32:10.908 --> 01:32:12.668
light, radiating light,

01:32:13.109 --> 01:32:15.550
and that he invited us

01:32:16.837 --> 01:32:19.298
to listen to Yahowah so that we could

01:32:19.359 --> 01:32:23.962
follow him to this same result that causes

01:32:24.143 --> 01:32:27.786
us to be glorified and to become great.

01:32:29.067 --> 01:32:33.489
And that is worth our attention.

01:32:33.569 --> 01:32:35.372
And I'm glad that we invested this time

01:32:35.412 --> 01:32:37.974
and we're going through this deliberately,

01:32:38.054 --> 01:32:41.516
methodically, intellectually,

01:32:42.478 --> 01:32:45.000
capitalizing on all that our great king

01:32:45.140 --> 01:32:46.280
and savior had to say.

01:32:47.250 --> 01:32:49.112
And so we'll return to

01:32:49.152 --> 01:32:51.654
Mizmowr's song, Psalm thirty four five.

01:32:53.036 --> 01:32:55.738
And our next program of Gabor.

